The Blessed One saw Ven Piṇḍola Bhāradvāja sitting not far away his legs crossed his body held erecta wilderness dweller an almsgoer a ragrobe wearer an owner of only one set of three robes modest content solitary unentangled his persistence aroused an advocate of the ascetic practices devoted to the heightened mind
