Its a form of abuse in the world to say You go around as an alms gatherer with a bowl in your hand Yet reasonable young men of good families have taken it up for a compelling reason
They have not been forced into it by kings or robbers nor through debt through fear nor through the loss of their livelihood
but through the thought We are beset by birth aging  death by sorrows lamentations pains distresses  despairs beset by stress overcome with stress O that the end of this entire mass of suffering  stress might be known
